## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent complexity of legal and ethical issues surrounding organ transplantation. The variability in international laws and practices also presents challenges in drawing universal conclusions. Further research is needed to explore the impact of recent legal amendments and technological advancements on organ donation and transplantation practices.